:::summary
The skilled trades — carpentry, masonry, plumbing, electrical work, welding, and dozens of others — are among the most essential and dignified forms of human work. From the stone masons who built the great cathedrals of Europe to the craftsmen who frame houses and lay pipe in American neighborhoods today, the trades represent the indispensable partnership of mind and hand that builds and maintains civilization. A proper classical and Christian education honors the dignity of skilled labor and recognizes that working with one's hands in service of one's neighbors is a high and honorable calling.
